Interface Graph<V,E>

All Known Implementing Classes:
TreeMapGraph
public interface Graph<V,E>
This interface defines the functionality of an undirected graph where elements can be stored in vertices and edges.
Version:
November 2014

    • insertEdge

      Edge<E> insertEdge(Vertex<V> u, Vertex<V> v, E e)
      Inserts an edge in the graph, defined by vertex u and v and storing element e. If the graph already contains an edge with the key corresponding to the element e no new edge is added. If no edge stores an element with the same key than e, a new adge is created and added. If one of the nodes used to define the edge does not exist in the graph it is created and inserted.
      Parameters:
      u - First node defining the edge
      v - Second node defining the edge
      e - The element to store in the edge
      Returns:
      The edge created

    • insertEdge

      Edge<E> insertEdge(Element u, Element v, E e)
      Inserts an edge in the graph, defined by elements u and v (for the vertices) and storing element e (in the edge). If the graph already contains an edge with the key corresponding to the element e no new edge is added. If no edge stores an element with the same key than e, a new adge is created and added. If one of the nodes used to define the edge does not exist in the graph it is created and inserted.
      Parameters:
      u - Element defining the first node used to define the edge
      v - Element defining the second node used to define the edge
      e - The element to store in the edge
      Returns:
      The edge created

    • opposite

      Vertex<V> opposite(Vertex<V> v, Edge<E> edge)
      Provides the vertex opposite to one provided on the edge given. If the vertex used as parameter does not belong to the edge a null value is returned
      Parameters:
      v - The node whose opposite we want
      edge - The edge used to obtain the opossite
      Returns:
      The vertex opposite to the one used as parameter on the given edge or null if the node v does not belong to the edge
